intro: Seseli praecox, commonly known as early seseli, is a flowering plant belonging to the Apiaceae family. It is characterized by its slender, branched stems and small, greenish-white flowers that bloom in early spring. The plant typically grows in open, disturbed habitats such as roadsides and meadows. Its leaves are finely divided and resemble those of other members of the carrot family. Seseli praecox is often found in temperate regions of Europe and parts of Asia.
